<title>USA: INTERVIEW - Applied sees $100 mln in savings.</title>
<headline>INTERVIEW - Applied sees $100 mln in savings.</headline>
<byline>Brendan Intindola</byline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-02-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Applied Magnetics Corp's proposed $1.8 billion stock-swap merger with Read-Rite Corp would yield $100 million in savings by September, the end of both companies' fiscal year, Applied's chairman and chief executive said on Monday.</p>
<p>At that level, the deal would be 11 percent accretive to fiscal 1997 earnings, Craig Crisman said in an interview.</p>
<p>The unsolicited bid was based only on publicly available information, Crisman said, meaning Applied has not reviewed Read-Rite's confidential financials in formulating the offer.</p>
